		<td><b>Processor speed-up during gameplay</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />There's something that's been bugging me.  On the last level of Dr. Jekyll and Mr. Hyde, there's a point in the game when the processor speeds up.  It happens only on one part, and that's when you get to the first singing lady.  Also, it doesn't happen all the time.  It speeds EVERYTHING up, the barrels, the lady, music notes from the lady,  and your character.  Why would this occur?  Any ideas?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
